me consuming and wages are flexible, search frictions--the cost of a job search--act like labor adjustment costs, further exacerbating inconsistencies between the competitive model and data. The book shows that wage rigidities can reconcile the search model with the data, providing a quantitatively more accurate depiction of labor markets, consumption, and investment dynamics. Developing detailed search and matching models, Labor Markets and Business Cycles will be the main reference for those interested in the intersection of labor market dynamics and business cycle research.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aBUSINESS and ampxECONOMICSvLabor. 0aBusiness cycles. 0aLabor market. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Labor.2bisacsh1 aCiccone, Antonio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGalí, Jordi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVentura, Jaume, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVoth, Hans-Joachim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311044250240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781400835232zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781400835232423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781400835232.jpg  a978-3-11-044250-2  Princeton University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK